  "stem": "<p>Let n = p + q. Which of the following is equivalent to z<sup>2</sup> &minus; p<sup>2</sup> &minus; 2pq &minus; q<sup>2</sup>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>(z &minus; n)(z + n)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>(z + n)<sup>2</sup></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p>(z &minus; n)<sup>2</sup></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p>z<sup>2</sup> &minus; nz &minus; n<sup>2</sup></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "a"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Note that p<sup>2</sup> + 2pq + q<sup>2</sup> = (p + q)<sup>2</sup> = n<sup>2</sup>. So z<sup>2</sup> &minus; p<sup>2</sup> &minus; 2pq &minus; q<sup>2</sup> = z<sup>2</sup> &minus; n<sup>2</sup> = (z &minus; n)(z + n). The other choices come from sign errors or from forgetting the middle term.</p>",
